                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13534808" author="rmeyer" created="Tue, 18 Dec 2012 10:21:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached a patch containing a small change to remove scaling from XGC when getting image info as it is now handled from a single location by FOP.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13535975" author="cbowditch" created="Wed, 19 Dec 2012 14:04:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Rob,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for your patch. I&apos;ve moved the issue into XGC where this patch applies.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Chris&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13543969" author="rmeyer" created="Fri, 4 Jan 2013 15:53:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have attached 5 files showing this issue. The first of these is output-72-wo-xgc-fop-patches.pdf. This file displays everything using 72 which uses the default image size. As you can see, the image with the rainbow is double the size of the two red squares. Note that the two redsquare images are SVG whereas the rainbow image is a normal bitmap.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;output-144-wo-xgc-patch.pdf shows that due to the changes made in FOP, all images are scaled, however the rainbow image is scaled twice resulting it being the same size as the SVG images now. This is because scaling occurred independently from FOP in XGC. Now that FOP handles scaling across both SVG and other image types, this is uneccessary.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Finally, we have output-144-with-xgc-fop-patches.pdf which shows the fix where the rainbow image is being scaled as expected.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have attached both the FO and XCONF for testing purposes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13544017" author="cbowditch" created="Fri, 4 Jan 2013 16:50:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Rob,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch itself looks fine. As Glenn suggested on fop-dev though we could do with a layout unit test to cover these changes. I think thats a reasonable suggestion since the changes affect layout. Can you attach a patch that adds layout unit tests?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Chris&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13546891" author="cbowditch" created="Tue, 8 Jan 2013 13:48:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Rob has raised &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FOP-2181&quot; title=&quot;[PATCH] Add a test case for the recent fix made in FOP-2174 and XGC-76 regarding source resolution scaling with SVG and images&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FOP-2181&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FOP-2181&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to add a unit test for the changes in FOP, so I will go ahead and commit this part of the bug fix too.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13546895" author="cbowditch" created="Tue, 8 Jan 2013 13:53:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch applied in revision: 1430286&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Many thanks for the contribution&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
